cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for image classification using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a new architecture with gated mechanisms and hybrid connectivity, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions using multi-kernel depthwise convolutions, which are related to neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on various datasets, including MS-COCO, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
